thread.title: High School football capsules: Week 5

title: High School football capsules: Week 5
text:
Watertown (2-2, 1-1) vs. Carthage (2-2, 1-1) 
When, where: 7 p.m., Carthage. 
Outlook: The suddenly surging Cyclones will take on the Comets, with the winner moving into sole possession of second-place in the divisional standings. … Watertown has won two straight games, including a thrilling 41-33 over win over New Hartford last Friday. Carthage, meanwhile, suffered a letdown with an interdivision loss to Jamesville-DeWitt last week, after snapping Indian River’s 15-game winning streak the week prior. … The Carthage defense has allowed a division-low 31 points in its pair of league games, but will face a tough test in the form of Watertown running back Daesean Williams. The senior is averaging 201 rushing yards in his last three games and has scored seven touchdowns in that span, including a 14-yard run with 12 seconds left to clinch last Friday’s win. … Carthage has won the last three games in the series between area rivals. Watertown’s last victory over Carthage came in 2011. 
New Hartford (0-4, 0-2) vs. Indian River (2-2, 1-2) 
When, where: 7 p.m., Philadelphia. 
Class B East 
South Jefferson (1-3, 1-3) vs. Vernon-Verona-Sherrill (3-1, 3-0) 
When, where: 7 p.m., Adams. 
Class B-C crossover 
General Brown (4-0, 3-0) vs. Oneida (2-2, 2-2) 
When, where: 7 p.m., Oneida. 
Class C North 
Lowville (2-2, 1-2) vs. Thousand Islands (4-0, 2-0) 
When, where: 7 p.m., Clayton. 
Outlook: In the NNY Game of the Week, the Vikings look to stay unbeaten in the first of three straight games against area rivals to close the regular season. … Following tonight’s matchup with the Red Raiders, Thousand Islands will play Immaculate Heart, and close the regular season against fellow unbeaten General Brown. … TI senior Tyler Gilfus has completed 72 percent of his passes to go with a touchdown-to-interception ratio 5:1 through four games. He threw for a pair of TDs in last week’s 28-7 victory over Pulaski. … Patrick Garnder has emerged as a lead-back for Lowville, tallying 426 yards and four touchdowns on 64 carries. … The Vikings’ defense has yet to allow more than 14 points in any game this season. The Red Raiders are averaging more than 25 points scored through their first four games. 
Class D West 
Sandy Creek (2-2, 2-0) vs. Onondaga (4-0, 1-0) 
When, where: 7 p.m., Onondaga. 
NFF East Division 
South Lewis (0-4, 0-1) vs. Waterville (2-2, 1-0). 
When, where: 7 p.m., Turin.
